Electrical network study is important in network analysis
Transparent conducting electrodes are essential component of solar cells. It's role on solar cell performance is discussed.
/* Theory */
The topmost layer should be transparent and conducting for light transmission and charge carrier collection.
/* Conducting nanowire networks and  metal mesh as flexible transparent electrodes */

In past 3 years, conducting nanowires networks are emerging promising candidates of transparent electrodes. In these cases wire network is conducting while voids are transparent to light. The network geometry decides their transmittance and resistance.
